<h1 id="not-valuable-fixed-assets-nvfas-russia">Not valuable fixed assets (NVFAs) (Russia)</h1>


<p>Low-value, high-wear items that are used in the workplace can be tracked and accounted for as special types of fixed assets that are known as <em>not valuable fixed assets</em> (NVFAs). NVFAs are items that have a cost that is less than the specified cost limit. The full cost of NVFAs should be written off for depreciation in the first month of use.</p>
<p>When you purchase fixed assets, regular fixed assets and NVFAs are divided based on the purchase price (cost). The value that you set for the <strong>Max cost of the NVFA</strong> field when you <a href="#set-up-fixed-assets-parameters-for-nvfas">set up Fixed assets parameters for NVFAs</a> determines the cost that distinguishes regular fixed assets and NVFAs.</p>
<p>After you purchase and register NVFAs, you can perform the following tasks:</p>
<ul>
<li>Automate the process of putting NVFAs into operation and adding them to subsequent depreciation transactions.</li>
<li>Print the MB-2, MB-4, and MB-8 reports.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="set-up-fixed-assets-parameters-for-nvfas">Set up Fixed assets parameters for NVFAs</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to <strong>Fixed assets (Russia)</strong> &gt; <strong>Setup</strong> &gt; <strong>Fixed assets parameters</strong>.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Base value model</strong> field, select the default base value model.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Max cost of the NVFA</strong> field, enter the maximum limit for the cost of the NVFA.</li>
<li>In the <strong>NVFA inventory profile</strong> field, select the inventory profile for the NVFA.</li>
<li>On the <strong>Number sequences</strong> tab, in the <strong>Number sequence code</strong> field, select the number sequence code for the <strong>NVFA inventory number</strong> and <strong>NVFA issue journal number</strong> reference types.</li>
<li>On the <strong>Document</strong> tab, on the <strong>Document types</strong> FastTab, in the <strong>Number sequence code</strong> field, select the number sequence code for the <strong>NVFA Act on disposal (No. MB-4)</strong> and <strong>NVFA Act on writing-off No. MB-8)</strong> document types.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="set-up-fixed-asset-groups-for-nvfa">Set up fixed asset groups for NVFA</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to <strong>Fixed assets (Russia)</strong> &gt; <strong>Setup</strong> &gt; <strong>FA groups</strong>.</li>
<li>On the <strong>FA groups</strong> page, create a record, and fill in the fields. In the <strong>Type of group</strong> field, select <strong>NVFA</strong>.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="set-up-the-identification-of-fixed-asset-groups-for-nvfas">Set up the identification of fixed asset groups for NVFAs</h2>
<ol>
<li><p>Go to <strong>Fixed assets (Russia)</strong> &gt; <strong>Setup</strong> &gt; <strong>Working clothes/Special riggings/NVFA</strong> &gt; <strong>Identification of FA groups</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li><p>On the <strong>Condition for FA group identification</strong> page, create a record, and fill in the fields.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Select <strong>Compliance</strong>, and specify how the item is related to a fixed asset group.</p>
<div class="NOTE">
<h5>Note</h5>
<p>The system uses this setting to fill in the <strong>FA group</strong> and <strong>Lifetime</strong> fields on the <strong>Working clothes/Special riggings/NVFA issue journal lines</strong> page. For more information, see <a href="#generate-nvfa-records-putting-into-operation-transactions-and-depreciation-transactions-for-nvfas">Generate NVFA records, putting into operation transactions, and depreciation transactions for NVFAs</a>.</p>
</div>
</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="set-up-inventory-dimensions-for-nvfas">Set up inventory dimensions for NVFAs</h2>
<p>Use this procedure to set up inventory dimensions for NVFAs, working clothes, and special rigging items.</p>
<ol>
<li>Go to <strong>Product information management</strong> &gt; <strong>Setup</strong> &gt; <strong>Dimensions and variant groups</strong> &gt; <strong>Tracking dimension groups</strong>.</li>
<li>Create a dimension group.</li>
<li>For the <strong>Batch number</strong> dimension, select the <strong>Active</strong> check box to enable batch accounting for NVFAs. Items that have different prices are accounted for in different batches.</li>
<li>Also select the <strong>Primary stocking</strong> and <strong>Financial inventory</strong> check boxes for the <strong>Batch number</strong> dimension.</li>
<li>For the <strong>Serial number</strong> dimension, select the <strong>Active</strong> check box. This dimension is used when the asset is put into operation.</li>
<li>Also select the <strong>Blank receipt allowed</strong> and <strong>Blank issue allowed</strong> check boxes for the <strong>Serial number</strong> dimension. When these check boxes are selected, you can perform inventory operations without having to specify a serial number.</li>
<li>For the <strong>Inventory profile</strong> dimension, select the <strong>Active</strong> and <strong>Primary stocking</strong> check boxes to enable inventory profile accounting for NVFAs.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="set-up-items-as-nvfas">Set up items as NVFAs</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to <strong>Product information management</strong> &gt; <strong>Products</strong> &gt; <strong>Released products</strong>.</li>
<li>Create a new item, or double-click an existing item to open the item record.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Set up</strong> &gt; <strong>Dimension groups</strong> to set up storage and tracking dimension groups for the item.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Item model group</strong> field, select the item model group.</li>
<li>In the <strong>FA group</strong> field, select a fixed asset group that has the <strong>NVFA</strong> group type for the item.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="set-up-officials-for-the-nvfa-statement-of-writing-off-no-mb-8">Set up officials for the NVFA Statement of writing-off (No. MB-8)</h2>
<p>Use this procedure to set up the members and chairperson of the commission that is responsible for the NVFA Statement of writing off (No. MB-8).</p>
<ol>
<li>Go to <strong>Organization administration</strong> &gt; <strong>Setup</strong> &gt; <strong>Contacts</strong> &gt; <strong>Officials</strong>.</li>
<li>On the <strong>Fixed assets</strong> tab, select <strong>NVFA Statement of writing-off (No. MB-8)</strong>.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Add</strong> to create a record.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Position</strong> field, select <strong>Member</strong> or <strong>Chairman</strong> to indicate whether the selected employee is a commission member or the chairman. You can select only one employee as the chairman.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Name</strong> field, select the name of the employee.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="register-an-nvfa-by-using-a-purchase-order">Register an NVFA by using a purchase order</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to <strong>Accounts payable</strong> &gt; <strong>Common</strong> &gt; <strong>Purchase orders</strong> &gt; <strong>All purchase orders</strong>.</li>
<li>On the <strong>Action Pane</strong>, select <strong>New</strong> &gt; <strong>Purchase order</strong>.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Vendor account</strong> field, select the vendor account that you require, and then select <strong>OK</strong>.</li>
<li>Create a purchase order line.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Item number</strong> field, select an item number.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Quantity</strong> field, enter the quantity of the item that is being ordered.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Unit price</strong> field, enter the purchase price for an item unit. If the purchase price of a fixed asset is less than the value that is specified in the <strong>Max cost of the NVFA</strong> field on the <strong>Fixed assets parameters</strong> page, excluding the sales tax value, the item is considered an NVFA. In this case, the <strong>Inventory profile</strong> field on the <strong>Product</strong> tab of the <strong>Line details</strong> FastTab is automatically set to the value that is entered on the <strong>Fixed assets parameters</strong> page.</li>
<li>Post the vendor invoice.</li>
</ol>
<div class="NOTE">
<h5>Note</h5>
<p>If the system defines the item on the purchase line as an NVFA, you should not specify a fixed asset inventory number for that line in the purchase order.</p>
</div>
<h2 id="generate-nvfa-records-putting-into-operation-transactions-and-depreciation-transactions-for-nvfas">Generate NVFA records, putting into operation transactions, and depreciation transactions for NVFAs</h2>
<p>Use this procedure to automatically create NVFA records on the <strong>Not valuable FAs</strong> page (<strong>Fixed assets (Russia)</strong> &gt; <strong>Common</strong> &gt; <strong>Not valuable FAs</strong>), and to automatically create fixed asset journals for NVFA putting into operation and depreciation.</p>
<ol>
<li>Go to <strong>Fixed asset (Russia)</strong> &gt; <strong>Journals</strong> &gt; <strong>Working clothes/Special riggings/NVFAs issue</strong>.</li>
<li>Select <strong>New</strong> to create a journal, and fill in the fields.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Lines</strong>, and then select <strong>New</strong> to create a record.</li>
<li>Fill in the <strong>Item</strong> and <strong>Quantity</strong> fields. The values in the <strong>Person in charge</strong> and <strong>Location</strong> fields are filled in from the journal. The <strong>Lifetime</strong> and <strong>FA group</strong> fields are filled in automatically from the <strong>Condition for FA group identification</strong> page.</li>
<li>Verify and fill in the fields on the <strong>Product dimensions</strong> tab.</li>
<li>Close the <strong>Working clothes/Special rigging/NVFA issue journal lines</strong> page.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Close</strong> on the <strong>Working clothes/Special rigging/NVFA issue journal</strong> page. The system selects the <strong>Posted</strong> check box and creates fixed asset journals for NVFA putting into operation and depreciation.</li>
<li>Select <strong>FA journals</strong> &gt; <strong>FA journal (putting into operation)</strong> and <strong>FA journals</strong> &gt; <strong>FA journal (depreciation)</strong> to validate and post fixed asset journals.</li>
</ol>
<div class="NOTE">
<h5>Note</h5>
<p>The system creates records on the <strong>Not valuable FAs</strong> page after the fixed asset journal for NVFA putting into operation is posted.</p>
</div>
<h2 id="register-an-nvfa-by-using-the-not-valuable-fas-page">Register an NVFA by using the Not valuable FAs page</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to <strong>Fixed assets (Russia)</strong> &gt; <strong>Common</strong> &gt; <strong>Not valuable FAs</strong>.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Fixed asset</strong> to create an NVFA.</li>
<li>In the <strong>FA group</strong> field, select a fixed asset group for the NVFA.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Acquisition cost</strong> field, enter the acquisition amount for the fixed asset.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Note</strong> field, enter any additional information for the asset.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Resource</strong> field, select the resource or resource group that is assigned to the asset.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Fixed asset</strong> &gt; <strong>Componentry</strong> &gt; <strong>Componentry</strong>.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Add</strong> to create a line. In the <strong>Item number</strong> field, select an item.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Warehouse</strong> &gt; <strong>Dimensions display</strong> to enable the <strong>Batch number</strong> and <strong>Serial number</strong> dimensions for the item.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Batch number</strong> field, select a batch number for the item.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Serial number</strong> field, select a serial number for the item.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Initial quantity</strong> field, enter the initial quantity of the item that is used.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="generate-a-disposal-transaction-and-print-the-nvfa-statement-of-disposal-no-mb-4-from-the-fixed-asset-journal">Generate a disposal transaction and print the NVFA Statement of disposal (No. MB-4) from the fixed asset journal</h2>
<p>Use this procedure to generate and print the <strong>NVFA Statement of disposal (No. MB-4)</strong> report from the fixed asset journal after you enter disposal or writing-off transactions. For transactions that have a status of <strong>Written off</strong> or <strong>Written off (sale)</strong>, the report can also be printed from the <strong>Working clothes</strong>, <strong>Special rigging</strong>, or <strong>Not valuable FAs</strong> page. This report is generated by each department that uses working clothes, special rigging, and NVFAs.</p>
<div class="NOTE">
<h5>Note</h5>
<p>You can generate the report from the <strong>Working clothes</strong>, <strong>Special rigging</strong>, and <strong>Not valuable FAs</strong> pages only after you generate the report from the fixed asset journal.</p>
</div>
<ol>
<li>Go to <strong>Fixed assets (Russia)</strong> &gt; <strong>Journals</strong> &gt; <strong>FA journal</strong>.</li>
<li>Create a journal.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Name</strong> field, select the journal name.</li>
<li>Select <strong>Lines</strong> to open the <strong>Journal voucher</strong> page.</li>
<li>Select <strong>New</strong> to open the <strong>Add to journal</strong> dialog box.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Transaction date</strong> field, select the transaction date.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Transaction type</strong> field, select <strong>Disposal (sale)</strong>.</li>
<li>In the <strong>FA inventory number</strong> field, select the inventory number for the fixed asset.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Value model</strong> field, select the value model for the fixed asset.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Reason code</strong> field, select a reason code for the transaction.</li>
<li>In the <strong>Reason comment</strong> field, enter a comment or a description of the transaction.</li>
<li>Select <strong>OK</strong>. The write-off lines for all value models that are registered in the fixed assets account are created in the journal.
–or–</li>
</ol>
<p>Select <strong>Group operations</strong> &gt; <strong>Disposal (sale)</strong> after step 4 to create disposal transactions     .</p>
<ol start="5">
<li><p>In the <strong>Disposal date</strong> field, select the date of the disposal transaction.</p>
</li>
<li><p>On the <strong>Records to include</strong> tab, select <strong>Filter</strong>. Then specify the selection criteria that are used to create transactions.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Select <strong>OK</strong>, and then select <strong>OK</strong> again to create disposal or write-off transactions.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Select <strong>Validate</strong> &gt; <strong>Validate</strong> to validate the write-off transactions.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Select <strong>Post</strong> &gt; <strong>Post</strong> to post the transaction.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Close the page.</p>
</li>
<li><p>On the <strong>FA journal</strong> page, select <strong>Print</strong> &gt; <strong>NVFA Statement of disposal (No. MB-4)</strong> to open the <strong>NVFA Statement of disposal (No. MB-4)</strong> page.</p>
<div class="NOTE">
<h5>Note</h5>
<p>The <strong>Print</strong> button is available only for journals that have been posted. The written-off transaction that is created on the <strong>Journal voucher</strong> page appears on the <strong>Overview</strong> tab. This transaction has a document number. The document number is generated based on the number sequence that is set up on the <strong>Fixed assets parameters</strong> page.</p>
</div>
</li>
<li><p>In the <strong>Comment</strong> field, enter the reason for disposal.</p>
</li>
<li><p>On the <strong>Rows</strong> tab, you can view the document number, fixed asset number, and value model code.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Select <strong>Print</strong> to generate the <strong>NVFA Statement of disposal (No. MB-4)</strong> report.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="generate-a-writing-off-transaction-and-print-the-nvfa-statement-of-writing-off-no-mb-8-from-the-fixed-asset-journal">Generate a writing-off transaction and print the NVFA Statement of writing off (No. MB-8) from the fixed asset journal</h2>
<p>Use this procedure to generate and print the <strong>NVFA Statement of writing off (No. MB-8)</strong> report from the fixed asset journal after you enter writing-off or disposal transactions. For transactions that have a status of <strong>Written off</strong> or <strong>Written off (dismantlement)</strong>, the report can also be printed from the <strong>Working clothes</strong>, <strong>Special rigging</strong>, or <strong>Not valuable FAs</strong> page.</p>
<ol>
<li><p>Go to <strong>Fixed assets (Russia)</strong> &gt; <strong>Journals</strong> &gt; <strong>FA journal</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Create a journal.</p>
</li>
<li><p>In the <strong>Name</strong> field, select a journal name.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Select <strong>Lines</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Select <strong>New</strong> to open the <strong>Add to journal</strong> dialog box.</p>
</li>
<li><p>In the <strong>Transaction date</strong> field, select the transaction date.</p>
</li>
<li><p>In the <strong>Transaction type</strong> field, select <strong>Writing-off</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li><p>In the <strong>FA inventory number</strong> field, select the inventory number of the fixed asset.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Select <strong>OK</strong>. The value model lines for the asset record are created in the journal.
–or–
Select <strong>Group operations</strong> &gt; <strong>Writing-off</strong> after step 4 to create writing-off transactions.</p>
</li>
<li><p>In the <strong>Disposal date</strong> field, select the date of the writing-off transaction.</p>
</li>
<li><p>On the <strong>Records to include</strong> tab, select <strong>Filter</strong>. Then specify the selection criteria that are used to create transactions.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Select <strong>OK</strong>, and then select <strong>OK</strong> again to create disposal or writing-off transactions.</p>
</li>
<li><p>On the <strong>Journal voucher</strong> page, select <strong>Validate</strong> &gt; <strong>Validate</strong> to validate the journal.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Select <strong>Post</strong> &gt; <strong>Post</strong> to post the journal.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Select <strong>Print</strong> &gt; <strong>NVFA Statement of writing-off (No. MB-8)</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li><p>On the <strong>Overview</strong> tab, in the <strong>Order number</strong> field, enter the order number that the writing-off transaction should be posted under. In the <strong>Resolution date</strong> field, select the order date.</p>
</li>
<li><p>On the <strong>Rows</strong> tab, you can verify the document number, fixed asset number, and value model code.</p>
</li>
<li><p>On the <strong>Officials</strong> tab, you can view details about the officials who were assigned on the <strong>Officials</strong> page. You can also modify the employee details, if modification is required.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Select <strong>Print</strong> to generate the <strong>NVFA Statement of writing off (No. MB-8)</strong> report.</p>
</li>
</ol>
